// Virtual main: exit code = m::check() = 42 iff BOTH the static `:F500` spec AND the dynamic
// `:[spec]` spec produce the correct, untruncated 502-byte result ("1." + 500 zeros) — the
// comparison against the expected length happens inside check() at full i64 precision, since a
// raw 502 could not survive as a POSIX process exit code (truncated mod 256). Any mismatch
// (stale truncating bug, wrong heap-fallback math, …) exits 0 instead.
//   teko build examples/regressions/format_precision_large && \
//     ./examples/regressions/format_precision_large/format_precision_large   # → exit 42
use m

m::check() to i32
